# Basic Psychopharmacology

Introductory educational notes on psychopharmacology for learners and healthcare professionals.

## Purpose

- Outline key concepts in psychopharmacology
- Support understanding of mechanisms of action and clinical use
- Provide structured, accessible content in Portuguese

## Planned subtopics

- Main classes of psychotropic medications
- Basic mechanisms of action
- Principles of dose titration and monitoring
- Common side effects and their management
- Drug interactions and safety considerations
- Special populations and clinical cautions

> Note: Content in this repository is for educational purposes only and does not replace formal clinical training, local protocols, or individualized medical care.
